The instructions are outdated. The Google Admin console has changed quite a bit since. You will have to play around with the navigation a bit in order to find something that closely matches the content. Unfortunately, some of the quizzes is navigation path related, so those answers will be based on the content provided.

The course has a heavy emphasis on memorising the click paths for accessing sections of the admin console.  The locations of some items such as Reports > Managing alerts have changed on the current admin console. The course content has not been updated accordingly. This means the student has to use outdated information to answer quiz questions. Use cases and scenarios are discuss at a very brief level. The reading material relies heavily on the Google support pages which can be accessed without enrolling in the course. The sections on Google Credential Provider for Windows and Domain management does a good job of summarizing features/options.

Maybe I was expecting more than a basic introduction but this is just a quick intro into Cloud Identity. From the course, it is clear that some features (like MDM) require Premium Cloud Identity but it is hard to get what you can do without Premium. Overall, a decent course to introduce the end user as super admin for using cloud services. There is much-outdated information in the actual course that either creates confusion and/or misunderstandings (e.g., the online domain portal interface has changed but the lessons address old templates used leaving the user to spend an inordinate time searching for correct correlations and intel)...a big problem. Due to the disjointed mixed elements discussed, testing elements are off and also confusing.

The content and the teachings are great and helpful, and they link to active documentation.
